<p>If you&rsquo;ve ever wondered how to get restaurant-quality crispy pork belly at home without deep frying, this recipe is your answer. These <strong>Air Fryer Honey Glazed Pork Belly Bites</strong> turn out perfectly golden and shatteringly crisp on the outside, juicy and tender on the inside, and finished with a sticky honey-soy-garlic glaze that you&rsquo;ll want to put on everything.</p>



<p>The best part? They cook in just 20 minutes in the air fryer, with hardly any splatter, no oil to discard, and almost zero cleanup. Whether you&rsquo;re serving them as a party appetizer, a rice bowl topping, or the star of a weeknight dinner, these little flavor bombs disappear fast.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img data-perfmatters-preload decoding="async" width="760" height="760" data-pin-description="Crispy, sticky, sweet, and savory &mdash; these Air Fryer Honey Glazed Pork Belly Bites are exactly the kind of recipe that turns a regular weeknight into something special. Make a batch, share with friends, and don&#039;t be surprised when they ask you for the recipe." data-pin-title="Air Fryer Honey Glazed Pork Belly Bites " src="https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-1-760x760.png" alt="Close-up of sticky honey glazed crispy pork belly bites showing caramelized edges and glossy sauce" class="wp-image-194451" srcset="https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-1-760x760.png 760w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-1-380x380.png 380w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-1-150x150.png 150w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-1-768x768.png 768w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-1-500x500.png 500w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-1-600x600.png 600w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-1-96x96.png 96w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-1.png 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) calc(100vw - 40px), 760px" fetchpriority="high"></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Why You&rsquo;ll Love This Recipe</strong></h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Faster than oven-roasted pork belly</strong> &mdash; no 2-hour braise, no overnight prep.</li>



<li><strong>Air fryer magic</strong> &mdash; renders the fat beautifully and crisps the edges without deep frying.</li>



<li><strong>Sticky honey glaze</strong> &mdash; the perfect balance of sweet, salty, and garlicky.</li>



<li><strong>Only 6 main ingredients </strong>&mdash; pantry staples you probably already have.</li>



<li><strong>Crowd-pleaser</strong> &mdash; works as an appetizer, main, or meal-prep protein.</li>



<li><strong>Naturally gluten-free friendly </strong>&mdash; just swap soy sauce for tamari.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Ingredients You&rsquo;ll Need</strong></h2>



<p>Here&rsquo;s what goes into the perfect batch of air fryer pork belly bites:</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="760" height="760" data-pin-description="Crispy, sticky, sweet, and savory &mdash; these Air Fryer Honey Glazed Pork Belly Bites are exactly the kind of recipe that turns a regular weeknight into something special. Make a batch, share with friends, and don&#039;t be surprised when they ask you for the recipe." data-pin-title="Air Fryer Honey Glazed Pork Belly Bites " src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;760&#039;%20height=&#039;760&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20760%20760&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Ingredients Air Fryer Honey Glazed Pork Belly Bites on kitchen table." class="wp-image-194452 perfmatters-lazy" data-src="https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-2-760x760.png" data-srcset="https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-2-760x760.png 760w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-2-380x380.png 380w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-2-150x150.png 150w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-2-768x768.png 768w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-2-500x500.png 500w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-2-600x600.png 600w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-2-96x96.png 96w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-2.png 1200w" data-sizes="(max-width: 800px) calc(100vw - 40px), 760px" /></figure>



<p><strong>For the pork belly:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Pork belly: </strong>skinless cubes for crispy juicy bites</li>



<li><strong>Avocado oil:</strong> coats pieces for even browning</li>



<li><strong>Kosher salt:</strong> enhances natural savory pork flavor</li>



<li><strong>Black pepper:</strong> adds mild heat and depth</li>



<li><strong>Garlic powder:</strong> gives warm savory garlic notes</li>



<li><strong>Smoked paprika:</strong> adds smoky bold flavor finish</li>
</ul>



<p><strong>For the honey glaze:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Honey:</strong> creates sweet sticky glossy coating</li>



<li><strong>Soy sauce:</strong> adds salty umami balance depth</li>



<li><strong>Rice vinegar:</strong> brings bright tangy flavor contrast</li>



<li><strong>Garlic:</strong> delivers bold sharp aromatic punch</li>



<li><strong>Fresh ginger: </strong>adds warm zesty kick flavor</li>



<li><strong>Red pepper flakes:</strong> optional heat for spice</li>



<li><strong>Sesame oil:</strong> adds rich nutty aroma finish</li>
</ul>



<p><strong>For the garnish:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Green onions:</strong> add fresh crisp flavor pop</li>



<li><strong>Sesame seeds: </strong>bring light crunch and texture</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Best Cut of Pork Belly for the Air Fryer</h2>



<p>For this recipe, <strong>skinless pork belly</strong> works best. The skin requires longer cooking to crisp up properly and can be tricky in an air fryer. Look for a slab with even layers of fat and meat &mdash; too lean and it&rsquo;ll be dry, too fatty and it can be greasy.</p>



<p>If your pork belly has skin on, you can either remove it with a sharp knife before cubing, or score it deeply and pat it bone-dry to help it crisp.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>How to Make Air Fryer Honey Glazed Pork Belly Bites</strong></h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="760" height="760" data-pin-description="Crispy, sticky, sweet, and savory &mdash; these Air Fryer Honey Glazed Pork Belly Bites are exactly the kind of recipe that turns a regular weeknight into something special. Make a batch, share with friends, and don&#039;t be surprised when they ask you for the recipe." data-pin-title="Air Fryer Honey Glazed Pork Belly Bites " src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;760&#039;%20height=&#039;760&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20760%20760&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Raw pork belly cubed into 1-inch pieces on a wooden cutting board for air fryer honey glazed pork belly bites" class="wp-image-194453 perfmatters-lazy" data-src="https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-3-760x760.png" data-srcset="https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-3-760x760.png 760w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-3-380x380.png 380w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-3-150x150.png 150w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-3-768x768.png 768w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-3-500x500.png 500w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-3-600x600.png 600w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-3-96x96.png 96w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-3.png 1200w" data-sizes="(max-width: 800px) calc(100vw - 40px), 760px" /></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Prep the Pork Belly</h4>



<p>Pat the pork belly cubes very dry with paper towels. <strong>This is the secret to maximum crispiness</strong> &mdash; any surface moisture turns to steam and prevents browning. Toss the cubes with oil, salt, pepper, garlic powder, and smoked paprika.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="760" height="760" data-pin-description="Crispy, sticky, sweet, and savory &mdash; these Air Fryer Honey Glazed Pork Belly Bites are exactly the kind of recipe that turns a regular weeknight into something special. Make a batch, share with friends, and don&#039;t be surprised when they ask you for the recipe." data-pin-title="Air Fryer Honey Glazed Pork Belly Bites " src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;760&#039;%20height=&#039;760&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20760%20760&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Seasoning raw pork belly cubes with salt, pepper, garlic powder, and smoked paprika in a glass mixing bowl" class="wp-image-194454 perfmatters-lazy" data-src="https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-4-760x760.png" data-srcset="https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-4-760x760.png 760w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-4-380x380.png 380w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-4-150x150.png 150w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-4-768x768.png 768w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-4-500x500.png 500w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-4-600x600.png 600w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-4-96x96.png 96w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-4.png 1200w" data-sizes="(max-width: 800px) calc(100vw - 40px), 760px" /></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Air Fry Until Crispy</h4>



<p>Arrange the pork belly cubes in a single layer in your air fryer basket &mdash; don&rsquo;t overcrowd them, or they&rsquo;ll steam instead of crisp. Air fry at <strong>400&deg;F (200&deg;C) for 15&ndash;18 minutes</strong>, shaking the basket every 5 minutes. The cubes should be deep golden brown with crispy edges.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="760" height="1140" data-pin-description="Crispy, sticky, sweet, and savory &mdash; these Air Fryer Honey Glazed Pork Belly Bites are exactly the kind of recipe that turns a regular weeknight into something special. Make a batch, share with friends, and don&#039;t be surprised when they ask you for the recipe." data-pin-title="Air Fryer Honey Glazed Pork Belly Bites " src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;760&#039;%20height=&#039;1140&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20760%201140&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Seasoned pork belly cubes arranged in a single layer inside an air fryer basket" class="wp-image-194455 perfmatters-lazy" data-src="https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Pork_Belly_Bites-5-760x1140.jpg" data-srcset="https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Pork_Belly_Bites-5-760x1140.jpg 760w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Pork_Belly_Bites-5-380x570.jpg 380w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Pork_Belly_Bites-5-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Pork_Belly_Bites-5-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Pork_Belly_Bites-5-1365x2048.jpg 1365w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Pork_Belly_Bites-5-scaled.jpg 1200w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Pork_Belly_Bites-5-150x225.jpg 150w" data-sizes="(max-width: 800px) calc(100vw - 40px), 760px" /></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Make the Honey Glaze</h4>



<p>While the pork belly cooks, whisk together honey, soy sauce, rice vinegar, minced garlic, ginger, red pepper flakes, and sesame oil in a small saucepan. Simmer over medium heat for 2&ndash;3 minutes until slightly thickened and glossy.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Toss and Serve</h4>



<p>Transfer the crispy pork belly bites to a large bowl, pour the warm glaze over the top, and toss to coat every piece. Garnish with green onions and sesame seeds. Serve immediately while the glaze is sticky and the pork is crisp.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="760" height="760" data-pin-description="Crispy, sticky, sweet, and savory &mdash; these Air Fryer Honey Glazed Pork Belly Bites are exactly the kind of recipe that turns a regular weeknight into something special. Make a batch, share with friends, and don&#039;t be surprised when they ask you for the recipe." data-pin-title="Air Fryer Honey Glazed Pork Belly Bites " src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;760&#039;%20height=&#039;760&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20760%20760&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Golden brown crispy air fryer pork belly bites fresh out of the air fryer basket" class="wp-image-194449 perfmatters-lazy" data-src="https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-760x760.png" data-srcset="https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-760x760.png 760w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-380x380.png 380w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-150x150.png 150w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-768x768.png 768w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-500x500.png 500w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-600x600.png 600w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-96x96.png 96w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-160x160.png 160w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites-320x320.png 320w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Air-Fryer-Honey-Glazed-Pork-Belly-Bites.png 1200w" data-sizes="(max-width: 800px) calc(100vw - 40px), 760px" /></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Pro Tips for Perfect Pork Belly Bites</strong></h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Dry the meat thoroughly.</strong> Wet pork belly will never crisp &mdash; pat it dry with paper towels before seasoning. </li>



<li><strong>Don&rsquo;t overcrowd the basket.</strong> Cook in two batches if needed. Single layer = maximum crisp. </li>



<li><strong>Shake the basket often.</strong> Every 4&ndash;5 minutes helps the cubes brown evenly on all sides. </li>



<li><strong>Glaze at the end, not before.</strong> Honey burns in the air fryer. Always toss with the glaze after cooking. </li>



<li><strong>Drain the rendered fat.</strong> Halfway through cooking, carefully pour off the fat that&rsquo;s collected in the drawer &mdash; it&rsquo;ll help the bites crisp up faster. </li>



<li><strong>Cut cubes uniformly.</strong> Even 1-inch pieces cook at the same rate.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Variations to Try</h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Spicy Korean-style:</strong> Add 1 tablespoon gochujang to the glaze.</li>



<li><strong>Sticky bourbon glaze:</strong> Swap rice vinegar for 1 tablespoon bourbon.</li>



<li><strong>Maple-mustard:</strong> Replace honey with maple syrup and add 1 teaspoon Dijon.</li>



<li><strong>Pineapple teriyaki:</strong> Add 2 tablespoons pineapple juice and 1 tablespoon mirin.</li>



<li><strong>Garlic parmesan:</strong> Skip the honey glaze and toss the crispy bites with melted butter, garlic, and grated parmesan.</li>
</ul>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="760" height="1140" data-pin-description="Crispy, sticky, sweet, and savory &mdash; these Air Fryer Honey Glazed Pork Belly Bites are exactly the kind of recipe that turns a regular weeknight into something special. Make a batch, share with friends, and don&#039;t be surprised when they ask you for the recipe." data-pin-title="Air Fryer Honey Glazed Pork Belly Bites " src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;760&#039;%20height=&#039;1140&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20760%201140&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Honey glazed pork belly bites served over jasmine rice in a ceramic bowl with chopsticks" class="wp-image-194456 perfmatters-lazy" data-src="https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Pork_Belly_Bites-15-760x1140.jpg" data-srcset="https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Pork_Belly_Bites-15-760x1140.jpg 760w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Pork_Belly_Bites-15-380x570.jpg 380w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Pork_Belly_Bites-15-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Pork_Belly_Bites-15-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Pork_Belly_Bites-15-1365x2048.jpg 1365w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Pork_Belly_Bites-15-scaled.jpg 1200w, https://forktospoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Pork_Belly_Bites-15-150x225.jpg 150w" data-sizes="(max-width: 800px) calc(100vw - 40px), 760px" /></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">What to Serve with Honey Glazed Pork Belly Bites</h2>



<p>These bites are wildly versatile. Try them with:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Steamed jasmine or coconut rice</strong> to soak up the glaze</li>



<li><strong>Asian slaw or quick pickled cucumbers</strong> to cut the richness</li>



<li><strong>Bao buns or steamed dumpling wrappers</strong> for sliders</li>



<li><strong>Lettuce cups</strong> with shredded carrots and herbs</li>



<li><strong>Fried rice or stir-fried noodles</strong> as a protein topper</li>



<li><strong>Roasted broccoli or bok choy</strong> for a balanced plate</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Storage and Reheating</h2>



<p><strong>Refrigerator:</strong> Store leftovers in an airtight container for up to 3 days.</p>



<p><strong>Reheating:</strong> Reheat in the air fryer at 375&deg;F for 3&ndash;4 minutes to bring back the crisp. Avoid the microwave &mdash; it makes the pork rubbery and the glaze too sticky.</p>



<p><strong>Freezing:</strong> I don&rsquo;t recommend freezing the glazed bites, as the texture suffers. You can freeze the cooked (unglazed) pork belly for up to 2 months and glaze it after reheating.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Frequently Asked Questions</strong></h2>



<p><strong>Can I use pork shoulder instead of pork belly? </strong>Pork shoulder works but won&rsquo;t have the same fatty, crispy texture. If using shoulder, increase the oil and cook a few minutes longer.</p>



<p><strong>Do I need to boil the pork belly first?</strong> No. Many traditional recipes blanch pork belly first, but the air fryer renders the fat well enough on its own. Boiling beforehand can actually make the meat too soft.</p>



<p><strong>Why isn&rsquo;t my pork belly crispy?</strong> The two most common culprits: the meat wasn&rsquo;t dry enough before air frying, or the basket was overcrowded. Pat thoroughly with paper towels, and cook in a single layer with space between cubes.</p>



<p><strong>Can I make this ahead? </strong>You can prep and season the cubes up to 24 hours ahead, and mix the glaze ingredients ahead too. But for the best texture, air fry and toss with glaze right before serving.</p>



<p><strong>What size air fryer works best? </strong>A 5&ndash;6 quart air fryer comfortably holds 1.5 lbs of pork belly in a single layer. For smaller baskets, cook in two batches.</p>



<p><strong>Is this recipe gluten-free? </strong>Make it gluten-free by swapping soy sauce for tamari or coconut aminos. Everything else is naturally gluten-free.</p>



